<L>__{exterior boulevard evening}
<A>__{louis and claudia walk along a boulevard like father and daughter. all around them are bourgeois parisian families on their evening stroll. claudia points at the children that pass.}
<C>__{claudia}
<D>__{have i anything in common with her, louis?}
<A>__{she points to a beautiful french child walking by with her mother.}
<C>__{claudia}
<D>__{or her, or her or any of them?}
<C>__{louis}
<D>__{claudia, you torture yourself.}
<C>__{claudia}
<D>__{they are ducklings, that will grow into swans. whereas i must be the duckling forever.}
<C>__{louis}
<D>__{you are more beautiful than any of them.}
